news.title: Dalmia Nisus Finance invests over Rs 125 crore in Puranik Builders' two projects
news.para: The residential projects—Rumah Bali and Tokyo Bay—are spread over a total 30 acres with cumulative development potential of over 3.2 million sq ft in Thane’s Ghodbunder Road and Anand Nagar localities.

news.title: China's Zhenro warns of big annual loss as real estate crisis bites
news.para: Cash-strapped Zhenro is expected to post an attributable loss of between 12.5 billion yuan ($1.82 billion) and 13.5 billion yuan for the year ended Dec. 31, compared with a profit of 809 million yuan recorded a year earlier.

news.title: Homebuilder Lennar beats profit estimates on strong property prices
news.para: Home demand shot up across the United States when pandemic-era remote work trends allowed people to look for more affordable properties away from big cities, boosting the margins of homebuilders such as Lennar and D.R. Horton Inc.

news.title: Corporation collects 43% of property tax arrears as fiscal nears end in Coimbatore
news.para: The corporation had managed to collect only 38% of tax arrears last year. In the beginning of the current financial year, the arrear amount was 103 crore, of which 44.56 crore has been collected so far.

news.title: China's property sector draws closer to exit from protracted slump
news.para: Home sales by floor area in the first two months of 2023 fell 3.6% from a year earlier, according to data from the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS), compared with a 24% decline for the whole of 2022.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body recovers Rs 7 lakh in special property tax camps
news.para: Joint commissioner Kulpreet Singh said March 31 is the deadline to pay property tax, after which the residents will have to pay 20% penalty and 18% annual interest on the delayed payment.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body razes five illegal buildings
news.para: ​The owners were constructing the buildings without getting building plans approved from the civic body and in violation of building bylaws.

news.title: Applications for property valuation to go online today in Gujarat
news.para: A statement by the office of the Superintendent of Stamps and Registration Inspector said all property valuation applications would be processed in 10 days on the new digitized system.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP to check on suspension of three affordable projects soon
news.para: Senior DTCP officials and representatives of the developer — Ocean Seven Buildtech (OSB) — as well as over 50 homebuyers are likely to attend the meeting on Wednesday.

news.title: Delhi civic body to rope in drones to survey properties in industrial areas for tax assessment
news.para: The MCD has invited bids to conduct a drone-based survey through an agency for the purpose of tax assessment. The last date to submit a bid is March 16.

news.title: Not paid tax dues? Gurugram civic body set to serve notices to defaulters, seal properties
news.para: Moreover, the commissioner also asked the officials to recheck the properties which have been registered for change in use. Around 1,244 commercial properties have changed their use to residential properties, causing revenue loss to the civic body.

news.title: Jaipur development body removes squatters from 25 bighas spread over two sites in zone 12
news.para: In Sukhsagar Enclave on Kalwar road, officials cleared encroachments from three bighas of JDA land where a river drain was covered after levelling the soil and constructing a tin shed room over it.

news.title: Karnataka yet to resolve incorrect property tax claims on over 78,000 citizens
news.para: However, administrative delays continue, and citizens pointed out that they are still receiving penalty notifications on account of glitches in the BBMP.

news.title: UP discom & RWAs at loggerheads over replacement of meters in gated societies
news.para: According to PVVNL statistics, around 380 residential societies are there in 14 districts under PVVNL, out of which 90% are in Noida and Ghaziabad.

news.title: Not paying rent transit for SRA project akin to oppression: Bombay HC
news.para: The HC also instituted suo motu (on its own) civil contempt of court proceedings against one of the builders for breach of an undertaking to deposit by March 10, Rs 4 crore towards initial payment of transit rent to slumdwellers.
